                        Information Sources at ATSDR

   HazDat Database - Contains information about waste sites where ATSDR
   has been active, including a list of contaminants, and links to site
   documents
   Science Page - Gateway to environmental health information and
   resources
   Maps of Hazardous Waste Sites "GATHER" - A Geographic Analysis Tool for
   Health and Environmental Research which provides members of the public
   health community and general public access to spatial data pertinent to
   the analysis and exploration of public health issues

   Information Center - provides public service and scientific, managerial
   and technical information support via the ATSDR Clearinghouse,
   Toll-Free Number, Library, Master Mail Key, and Division of Toxicology
   Docket. To contact the Information Center, call 1-888-42-ATSDR
   (1-888-422-8737), e-mail atsdric@cdc.gov, or send a fax to
   404-498-0057.
